# Intentionally parallel code — structurally identical by design.
# A pair is suppressed only when BOTH functions match the SAME pattern.
# Pattern syntax: filepath.Match globs against function names (e.g., "(Type).Method*").

# Event logger methods — each Log* method wraps l.Log() with event-specific data.
# They are parallel by design; flagging them as clones buries real findings.
(Logger).Log*

# Event logger adapter methods — same pattern as Logger.
(EventLoggerAdapter).Log*
